domainIncludes.comment: A piece of equipment used to hold, protect or secure cargo for logistics purposes.,A referenced piece of equipment used to hold, protect or secure cargo for logistics purposes.TBR: description update to excersize GitHub update
A significant occurrence or happening during transport.,A referenced significant occurrence or happening during transport.
A service associated with a transport movement.,A referenced service associated with a specified event during transport movement.

A self-contained wrapping or container within which goods can be contained for logistics purposes, such as a box or a barrel which can be filled, partially filled or empty.,A referenced self-contained wrapping or container within which goods can be contained for logistics purposes.
The conveyance (physical carriage) of goods or other objects used for logistics transport purposes.
The devices used to convey goods or other objects from place to place during logistics cargo movements.

A separately identifiable collection of goods items to be transported or available to be transported from one consignor to one consignee in a supply chain via one or more modes of transport where each consignment is the subject of one single transport contract.,A referenced, separately identifiable collection of goods items to be transported or available to be transported from one consignor to one consignee via one or more modes of transport where each consignment is the subject of one single transport contract.

A reference to an item within a supply chain consignment of goods separately identified for transport and customs purposes.,An item within a supply chain consignment of goods separately identified for transport and customs purposes.
Any wrapping or containment, such as a box or a barrel, whether or not any goods are contained within.
Handling information of an instructive nature.
A logistics related physical location or place.
An IOT (Internet of Things) piece of mechanical or electronic equipment which can collect, report and autonomously transmit digital data.
A transport related person, such as a member of a crew or a passenger.
A way or course taken from one location to another for the purpose of transporting cargo and or passengers.
Reference to a device or method used to convey people, goods, or other objects from place to place.
A label used for identifying goods for logistics purposes, such as a barcode, a radio frequency tag or a Vehicle Identification Number (VIN).
A location where a transport service takes place.
An object which can detect and measure physical properties and which can record, indicate and transmit such measurements.
An individual, a group, or a body having a role related to a location.
The identification of related information in a supply chain context.
A significant occurrence or happening in a supply chain.
Hardware or software typically marketed by a company other than the original manufacturer.
